 sexuality, religion, gender and oral history, but anyone interested in social and cultural change more broadly.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCatholic womenxSexual behaviorxEnglandxHistoryy20th century. 0aContraceptionxReligious aspectsxCatholic Church. 0aSexxReligious aspectsxCatholic Church. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Catholic.2bisacsh  aCatholicism.  aContraception.  aGender.  aModernity.  aOral history.  aPost-war.  aReligion.  aSex.  aThe Pill.  aWomen.1 aGeiringer, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613839240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526138392423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526138392/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles